nk:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530643\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530643\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104olx1665702612615.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/olx1665702612615.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/olx1665702612615.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"olx1665702612615\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                    \n Form Size and Position \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The initial size and position of a form are set in the Uniface IDE using the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Height</span>, <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Width</span>, <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Top</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Left</span> properties in the Properties Inspector of the component. Form height and width are made visible at design time using a blue dashed bottom and right border on the Form canvas, if both <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Height</span>, <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Width</span> have a value &gt; 0.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"olx1665702612615__context_w377ab1b5b1_w378ab1b5_w379ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"olx1665702612615__p_d24491e1_d24492e1_d24493e1\">The value of these properties is specified in terms of number of characters, and the character size is determined by the canvas font (Font 0) which is set in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> file. Therefore, changing the canvas font can affect the appearance of the form.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"olx1665702612615__p_d24494e1_d24495e1_d24496e1\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Height</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Width</span> properties affect the component canvas, but the runtime form may differ because it is affected by the following factors, in order of priority:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"olx1665702612615__li_d12176e1_d12177e1_d12178e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The value of the Dimension property when dynamically set in ProcScript using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$windowproperties</span>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"olx1665702612615__li_d12179e1_d12180e1_d12181e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"olx1665702612615__p_d24497e1_d24498e1_d24499e1\">The value of the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Dimension</span>\n               property supplied as a parameter to the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">newinstance</span> command. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"olx1665702612615__li_d12182e1_d12183e1_d12184e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The value of <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Cell Height</span> window property as set declaratively.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"olx1665702612615__li_d12185e1_d12186e1_d12187e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The value of the CellHeight window property as set in the initialization file.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"olx1665702612615__li_d12188e1_d12189e1_d12190e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The size needed to show all entities and fields drawn on the component.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"olx1665702612615__li_d12191e1_d12192e1_d12193e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The size of the application window. When required, Uniface resizes the form. If the form is bigger than the application window, it is truncated and scroll bars appear on the form.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"olx1665702612615__result_w380ab1b5b5_w381ab1b5_w382ab1\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"olx1665702612615__note_kpz_mnr_rcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"olx1665702612615__ul_edf_nnr_rcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"olx1665702612615__li_d12194e1_d12195e1_d12196e1\">When using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\"></span> property, values\n                  must be expressed as the number of pixels, not the number of characters. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"olx1665702612615__li_d12197e1_d12198e1_d12199e1\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Height</span> and\n                     <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Width</span> properties do not take into account the size of\n                  panel and/or menus, whereas <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$windowproperties</span> does. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"olx1665702612615__li_d12200e1_d12201e1_d12202e1\">To have Windows handle positioning, set both\n                     <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Top</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Left</span> to\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code> for all forms. When multiple forms are displayed, Windows\n                  stacks them in an offset cascade, with each form displayed one position below and\n                  to the right of the previous form. If there are too many open forms, the stack\n                  continues to the bottom of the application window and begins again at top left\n                  position. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kfu1665702580321.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Dimension</a><p>Specifies a comma-separated string that defines the position and size of the form window in pixels.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bch1665702773514.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$windowproperties</a><p>Set or return the current window properties of a Form instance.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ryt1665702577808.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>newinstance</a><p>Creates a new instance of a component.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530643\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530643\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Form Size and Position Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Form Size and Position The initial size and position of a form are set in the Uniface IDE using the Height , Width , Top and Left properties in the Properties Inspector of the component. Form height and width are made visible at design time using a blue dashed bottom and right border on the Form canvas, if both Height , Width have a value > 0. The value of these properties is specified in terms of number of characters, and the character size is determined by the canvas font (Font 0) which is set in the usys.ini file. Therefore, changing the canvas font can affect the appearance of the form. The Height and Width properties affect the component canvas, but the runtime form may differ because it is affected by the following factors, in order of priority: The value of the Dimension property when dynamically set in ProcScript using $windowproperties . The value of the Dimension property supplied as a parameter to the newinstance command. The value of Cell Height window property as set declaratively. The value of the CellHeight window property as set in the initialization file. The size needed to show all entities and fields drawn on the component. The size of the application window. When required, Uniface resizes the form. If the form is bigger than the application window, it is truncated and scroll bars appear on the form. Note: When using the property, values must be expressed as the number of pixels, not the number of characters. The Height and Width properties do not take into account the size of panel and/or menus, whereas $windowproperties does. To have Windows handle positioning, set both Top and Left to 0 for all forms. When multiple forms are displayed, Windows stacks them in an offset cascade, with each form displayed one position below and to the right of the previous form. If there are too many open forms, the stack continues to the bottom of the application window and begins again at top left position. Related Links Dimension Specifies a comma-separated string that defines the position and size of the form window in pixels. $windowproperties Set or return the current window properties of a Form instance. newinstance Creates a new instance of a component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}